WEBVTT

00:22.021 --> 00:26.902
[alarm beeping]

00:31.699 --> 00:35.452
[birds singing]

00:35.577 --> 00:37.913
[woman on phone]

00:35.577 --> 00:37.913
<i>Laura, it's fine, I'll see you</i>

00:35.577 --> 00:37.913
<i>at the office.</i>

00:38.038 --> 00:39.289
I'll be there soon.

00:42.584 --> 00:44.795
-[man] Morning, Chip.

00:42.584 --> 00:44.795
-Hey, man!

00:47.673 --> 00:50.217
-Morning, Laura.

00:47.673 --> 00:50.217
-Morning, Frank.

00:50.342 --> 00:53.470
Oh! I heard you pulled out

00:50.342 --> 00:53.470
all the stops to save

00:50.342 --> 00:53.470
the Peterson account.

00:53.595 --> 00:55.389
They'll have to make you

00:53.595 --> 00:55.389
partner now.

00:55.514 --> 00:58.141
I hope so. There's a lot

00:55.514 --> 00:58.141
of changes I'd like to make.

00:58.266 --> 01:01.395
Like getting you that raise

00:58.266 --> 01:01.395
you should've gotten last year.

01:15.242 --> 01:17.411
Congratulations, Laura.

01:15.242 --> 01:17.411
You did it.

01:17.536 --> 01:19.621
Oh, I'd like to review the

01:17.536 --> 01:19.621
contract one last time, Fiona.

01:19.747 --> 01:22.123
Laura, it's perfect,

01:19.747 --> 01:22.123
they've signed it. It's done.

01:22.249 --> 01:25.210
-They've signed it? Already?

01:22.249 --> 01:25.210
-Yes, it's time to celebrate.

01:25.335 --> 01:28.756
So as your boss,

01:25.335 --> 01:28.756
I am ordering you to brag.

01:28.881 --> 01:31.926
Tell everyone how you did it.

01:32.051 --> 01:35.345
Well, Mr. Peterson might run

01:32.051 --> 01:35.345
an international corporation,

01:35.470 --> 01:37.556
but he's a local

01:35.470 --> 01:37.556
businessman at heart.

01:37.681 --> 01:40.308
I explained the opportunity

01:37.681 --> 01:40.308
in local expansion

01:40.434 --> 01:41.936
and persuaded him not to sell.

01:42.061 --> 01:45.480
Local expansion worth

01:42.061 --> 01:45.480
250 million.

01:45.606 --> 01:46.648
[man] Wow.

01:46.774 --> 01:49.192
[employees applauding]

01:49.317 --> 01:51.528
He wanted what was best

01:49.317 --> 01:51.528
for the community.

01:51.653 --> 01:53.822
I just helped him to see that.

01:53.948 --> 01:56.283
Laura, you're always

01:53.948 --> 01:56.283
so modest.

01:56.408 --> 01:58.660
It's all thanks

01:56.408 --> 01:58.660
to my lucky charm.

01:58.786 --> 02:01.538
Because the long hours

01:58.786 --> 02:01.538
and late nights

02:01.663 --> 02:03.582
had nothing to do with it.

02:04.917 --> 02:06.835
On an entirely

02:04.917 --> 02:06.835
different subject,

02:06.961 --> 02:08.796
what do you know

02:06.961 --> 02:08.796
about Graham Finley?

02:08.921 --> 02:11.924
Graham Finley,

02:08.921 --> 02:11.924
billionaire, highly educated,

02:12.049 --> 02:14.259
international property

02:12.049 --> 02:14.259
developer,

02:14.384 --> 02:17.012
terrible at coconut toss.

02:17.137 --> 02:20.682
I told you that I grew up

02:17.137 --> 02:20.682
in Sapphire Cove until I was 12.

02:20.808 --> 02:24.061
Your idyllic childhood

02:20.808 --> 02:24.061
on a tropical island.

02:24.185 --> 02:25.813
How could I forget?

02:25.938 --> 02:27.314
I grew up with the Finley's.

02:27.439 --> 02:31.276
His grandson Chip was

02:27.439 --> 02:31.276
my best friend.

02:31.401 --> 02:33.236
We lost touch though.

02:33.361 --> 02:39.743
-Ah. That explains it.

02:33.361 --> 02:39.743
-Explains what?

02:39.868 --> 02:42.579
Why there's a billionaire

02:39.868 --> 02:42.579
in my office.

02:42.704 --> 02:44.915
Waiting for you.

02:46.708 --> 02:49.003
[Fiona] Mr. Finley.

02:49.878 --> 02:51.463
Laura Price.

02:51.588 --> 02:55.467
My goodness. All grown up.

02:55.592 --> 02:57.928
Mr. Finley, it's

02:55.592 --> 02:57.928
so wonderful to see you again.

02:58.053 --> 03:00.472
I remember when you

02:58.053 --> 03:00.472
and my grandson

03:00.597 --> 03:03.017
filled my Mercedes with seaweed.

03:03.142 --> 03:06.103
So it's a bit late

03:03.142 --> 03:06.103
for "Mr. Finley" now.

03:06.227 --> 03:08.271
Please.

03:08.396 --> 03:10.691
Well, I've heard

03:08.396 --> 03:10.691
all about your achievements

03:10.816 --> 03:12.400
from Mrs. Wilde here.

03:12.526 --> 03:14.444
The valedictorian.

03:14.569 --> 03:18.115
A portfolio

03:14.569 --> 03:18.115
of high-profile clients.

03:18.239 --> 03:20.492
A promotion waiting

03:18.239 --> 03:20.492
in the wings.

03:20.617 --> 03:23.829
You've certainly made your mark

03:20.617 --> 03:23.829
since leaving Sapphire Cove.

03:23.954 --> 03:26.373
Well, it's not as

03:23.954 --> 03:26.373
impressive as your legacy

03:26.498 --> 03:29.001
but I'm not finished yet.

03:29.126 --> 03:32.963
That's the Laura I remember.

03:29.126 --> 03:32.963
Ambitious and determined.

03:33.088 --> 03:36.800
You may not have noticed, Laura,

03:33.088 --> 03:36.800
but I've gotten old.

03:36.925 --> 03:39.553
I'm 85 soon.

03:39.678 --> 03:42.389
85 is a significant

03:39.678 --> 03:42.389
milestone, Mr. Finley.

03:42.514 --> 03:44.474
You see, I am CEO

03:42.514 --> 03:44.474
of the company

03:44.599 --> 03:47.936
until the day I choose

03:44.599 --> 03:47.936
to step down or...

03:48.062 --> 03:50.564
Or your 85th birthday,

03:48.062 --> 03:50.564
whichever comes first.

03:50.689 --> 03:52.440
Whichever comes first.

03:52.566 --> 03:54.693
The mandatory

03:52.566 --> 03:54.693
retirement clause.

03:54.818 --> 03:56.111
Retirement clauses

03:56.236 --> 03:59.031
are notoriously difficult

03:56.236 --> 03:59.031
to outmaneuver.

03:59.156 --> 04:01.366
Oh, it's much too late

03:59.156 --> 04:01.366
for any of that.

04:01.491 --> 04:04.578
My son was not a good fit.

04:04.703 --> 04:07.247
But it's not too late

04:04.703 --> 04:07.247
for my grandson.

04:07.372 --> 04:10.042
I want to name Chip my successor

04:10.167 --> 04:13.879
because it's my last chance to

04:10.167 --> 04:13.879
keep my business in the family.

04:14.004 --> 04:19.676
So he needs to sign on the

04:14.004 --> 04:19.676
dotted line before I turn 85.

04:19.801 --> 04:22.221
Laura can draw up

04:19.801 --> 04:22.221
a contract immediately.

04:22.345 --> 04:26.100
Good, because I need

04:22.345 --> 04:26.100
you to take it to him

04:26.225 --> 04:27.851
and get him to sign it.

04:27.976 --> 04:33.815
We don't have a lot of time here

04:27.976 --> 04:33.815
and he can be a little stubborn.

04:33.941 --> 04:36.484
You're the only one

04:33.941 --> 04:36.484
he's ever listened to.

04:36.610 --> 04:39.029
She'd be delighted to take

04:36.610 --> 04:39.029
the contract to Chip.

04:39.154 --> 04:43.700
Of course. Where exactly

04:39.154 --> 04:43.700
is Chip living these days?

04:44.826 --> 04:46.286
Well...

04:46.411 --> 04:47.621
Sapphire Cove?

04:47.746 --> 04:50.249
Now? I can't go now.

04:47.746 --> 04:50.249
It's been forever.

04:50.373 --> 04:52.292
I haven't spoken to Chip

04:50.373 --> 04:52.292
since I was a kid.

04:52.417 --> 04:54.086
I didn't even know

04:52.417 --> 04:54.086
what he looks like.

04:54.211 --> 04:56.004
Well, don't over

04:54.211 --> 04:56.004
complicate it.

04:56.130 --> 04:59.133
You fly over, find Chip,

04:56.130 --> 04:59.133
get the contract signed

04:59.258 --> 05:01.218
and you'll be back

04:59.258 --> 05:01.218
in a few days.

05:01.342 --> 05:03.178
Fiona, I have

05:01.342 --> 05:03.178
so much work to do,

05:03.303 --> 05:04.888
I'm going to be working late

05:03.303 --> 05:04.888
as it is.

05:05.013 --> 05:06.723
Why don't you take Owen?

05:06.848 --> 05:09.559
You two can spend some time

05:06.848 --> 05:09.559
together before the big day.

05:09.684 --> 05:11.686
Actually, we decided to push

05:09.684 --> 05:11.686
the date back again.

05:11.812 --> 05:12.896
Again?

05:13.021 --> 05:15.190
I know... We've been so busy.

05:15.315 --> 05:18.318
Besides, I thought that

05:15.315 --> 05:18.318
I would hear about

05:15.315 --> 05:18.318
the partnership soon.

05:18.443 --> 05:22.823
We're still in talks.

05:18.443 --> 05:22.823
It's down to you and Simon.

05:24.783 --> 05:27.452
-Simon?

05:24.783 --> 05:27.452
-Mmm-hm.

05:27.577 --> 05:30.956
He brings in big clients.

05:27.577 --> 05:30.956
That means big money.

05:31.081 --> 05:32.624
But what about my local

05:31.081 --> 05:32.624
business plan?

05:32.749 --> 05:34.375
Yeah, yeah, they loved it.

05:34.501 --> 05:37.171
More face-to-face time

05:34.501 --> 05:37.171
with clients,

05:37.296 --> 05:39.214
protect small businesses.

05:37.296 --> 05:39.214
They ate it up.

05:39.338 --> 05:43.927
But at the end of the day,

05:39.338 --> 05:43.927
money talks.

05:44.052 --> 05:46.596
Graham came to you for a reason.

05:46.721 --> 05:48.389
He really thinks

05:46.721 --> 05:48.389
you can persuade Chip.

05:48.515 --> 05:51.185
Bringing in a client

05:48.515 --> 05:51.185
like Graham Finley

05:51.310 --> 05:53.061
might just be the edge you need.

05:53.187 --> 05:55.480
-Do you think so?

05:53.187 --> 05:55.480
-I know so.

05:55.605 --> 05:58.692
Besides, there are worse places

05:55.605 --> 05:58.692
to end up

05:58.817 --> 06:01.278
than on a tropical island.

06:01.402 --> 06:05.907
Fine print is my specialty.

06:01.402 --> 06:05.907
Yeah, alright, fantastic.

06:06.033 --> 06:09.577
Honey, I am so sorry.

06:06.033 --> 06:09.577
I'm so snowed under right now.

06:09.703 --> 06:11.412
What were we talking about?

06:11.538 --> 06:14.082
We were talking

06:11.538 --> 06:14.082
about Sapphire Cove.

06:14.208 --> 06:15.917
Yes, yes, your hometown.

06:16.043 --> 06:17.252
I haven't been there

06:16.043 --> 06:17.252
since I was a kid.

06:17.376 --> 06:20.421
But this work thing

06:17.376 --> 06:20.421
kind of popped up

06:20.547 --> 06:25.177
and I thought that maybe

06:20.547 --> 06:25.177
we could go there together.

06:25.302 --> 06:26.845
Once I get this contract signed

06:26.970 --> 06:30.431
then we can just relax for once

06:26.970 --> 06:30.431
and it might be nice.

06:30.557 --> 06:33.185
I don't know, honey. I could

06:30.557 --> 06:33.185
really use the extra hours

06:30.557 --> 06:33.185
around the office right now.

06:33.310 --> 06:34.853
I just have to go there

06:34.978 --> 06:36.938
and get Chip Finley to sign

06:34.978 --> 06:36.938
this contract in person

06:37.064 --> 06:39.482
and then if all goes well,

06:39.607 --> 06:44.612
I might get the whole

06:39.607 --> 06:44.612
Finley account.

06:44.738 --> 06:47.448
You will get the whole

06:44.738 --> 06:47.448
Finley account.

06:47.574 --> 06:49.784
This is the big leagues now,

06:47.574 --> 06:49.784
honey.

06:49.910 --> 06:53.330
Look, I know you love

06:49.910 --> 06:53.330
all that charity work

06:49.910 --> 06:53.330
you're doing, but...

06:53.454 --> 06:56.166
Giving smaller clients more

06:53.454 --> 06:56.166
time isn't exactly charity work.

06:56.291 --> 06:58.752
It's what legal representation

06:56.291 --> 06:58.752
is meant to be about.

06:58.877 --> 07:00.712
Honey, remember, we're sharks.

07:00.837 --> 07:03.673
And think of this Finley

07:00.837 --> 07:03.673
account as your prey.

07:03.798 --> 07:07.219
We are always hunting.

07:03.798 --> 07:07.219
Keeping our eye on the prize.

07:07.344 --> 07:10.513
And then when

07:07.344 --> 07:10.513
it's in our sights...

07:10.638 --> 07:13.892
...that's when we pounce.

07:14.017 --> 07:17.771
Well, let's hope

07:14.017 --> 07:17.771
that Chip Finley

07:14.017 --> 07:17.771
isn't too hard to hunt down.

07:17.896 --> 07:18.855
You'll be great.

07:25.528 --> 07:27.155
[pilot]<i> Welcome</i>

07:25.528 --> 07:27.155
<i>to Sapphire Cove</i>

07:27.281 --> 07:29.324
<i>where the local time</i>

07:27.281 --> 07:29.324
<i>is 8:02 a.m.</i>

07:38.166 --> 07:40.919
Welcome to Sapphire Cove.

07:38.166 --> 07:40.919
If you make your way

07:38.166 --> 07:40.919
down to the pier,

07:41.044 --> 07:43.546
our captain is waiting

07:41.044 --> 07:43.546
to take you to the hotel.

07:43.671 --> 07:45.424
The captain?

07:45.548 --> 07:46.425
After you.

07:56.768 --> 07:58.937
[Laura] Well, this is one way

07:56.768 --> 07:58.937
to get around.

07:59.062 --> 08:00.397
Sure beats rush-hour traffic.

08:00.563 --> 08:03.150
-First time to the island?

08:00.563 --> 08:03.150
-Uh... No.

08:03.275 --> 08:05.110
But it's been a very long time.

08:05.235 --> 08:07.154
Well, better late than never.

08:07.279 --> 08:10.490
Let me guess. Lawyer.

08:10.615 --> 08:12.326
Oh! That obvious?

08:12.451 --> 08:14.828
Not everybody gets so dressed

08:12.451 --> 08:14.828
up to come on vacation.

08:14.953 --> 08:20.917
Right. Well, my turn.

08:14.953 --> 08:20.917
You must be... the captain.

08:21.835 --> 08:24.338
[scoffs] Lucky guess.

08:24.463 --> 08:25.588
-Dude...

08:24.463 --> 08:25.588
-What?

08:25.713 --> 08:28.967
-Your shirt!

08:25.713 --> 08:28.967
-Oh! Oh.

08:29.092 --> 08:31.178
[Chip]

08:29.092 --> 08:31.178
You could've told me earlier!

08:48.028 --> 08:50.197
There we go.

08:50.322 --> 08:52.991
[man] Welcome to the Royal

08:50.322 --> 08:52.991
Hotel. Mind your step.

08:53.116 --> 08:54.784
[woman] Welcome. Sparkling wine?

08:54.909 --> 08:55.910
[mumbling]

08:56.036 --> 08:59.206
Hi. How are you?

08:56.036 --> 08:59.206
So have a good trip.

08:59.331 --> 09:01.291
If you can, treat yourself

08:59.331 --> 09:01.291
to a pair of sandals.

09:01.416 --> 09:03.877
I hear they're much more

09:01.416 --> 09:03.877
comfortable than heels.

09:04.002 --> 09:06.087
I might just do that.

09:04.002 --> 09:06.087
Thank you.

09:06.213 --> 09:08.089
And if you need someone to

09:06.213 --> 09:08.089
take you around the island,

09:08.215 --> 09:09.632
we do offer guided tours.

09:09.757 --> 09:11.843
Actually, you might be

09:09.757 --> 09:11.843
able to help me...

09:11.968 --> 09:13.345
-Yoo-hoo.

09:11.968 --> 09:13.345
-What?

09:13.470 --> 09:15.805
Anybody home?

09:15.930 --> 09:17.724
-Welcome drink, ma'am?

09:15.930 --> 09:17.724
-Oh. Thank you.

09:17.849 --> 09:19.017
Take the bag!

09:19.142 --> 09:20.394
[Laura] Thank you.

09:20.519 --> 09:24.064
When you book at

09:20.519 --> 09:24.064
the front desk ask for Chip.

09:25.148 --> 09:26.024
Chip?

09:30.320 --> 09:32.447
[woman 2] This way, please.

09:32.572 --> 09:34.615
Your bag will be delivered

09:32.572 --> 09:34.615
straight to your room.

10:05.397 --> 10:11.445
"Dear Laura... A little taste of

10:05.397 --> 10:11.445
the high life. Enjoy. Fiona."

10:11.570 --> 10:13.029
Where's the Wi-Fi password?

10:13.154 --> 10:15.115
-[knock at the door]

10:13.154 --> 10:15.115
-[Gem] Laura?

10:15.240 --> 10:17.700
-I haven't seen you in so long.

10:15.240 --> 10:17.700
-Gem!

10:19.869 --> 10:21.662
When I saw your name

10:19.869 --> 10:21.662
on the reservation,

10:21.788 --> 10:23.831
I couldn't believe it.

10:21.788 --> 10:23.831
You came back.

10:23.957 --> 10:26.667
I did. It's been forever.

10:26.793 --> 10:30.589
Gosh, look at you all

10:26.793 --> 10:30.589
fancy and grown-up.

10:30.713 --> 10:32.424
Oh, yes, well,

10:30.713 --> 10:32.424
as assistant manager

10:32.549 --> 10:34.884
of the Royal Hotel, please

10:32.549 --> 10:34.884
do not hesitate to let me know

10:35.009 --> 10:37.387
if there is anything I can do to

10:35.009 --> 10:37.387
make your stay more enjoyable.

10:37.512 --> 10:40.765
Oh, I love this suite, by

10:37.512 --> 10:40.765
the way. It is my favorite.

10:40.890 --> 10:45.312
It's magnificent. I mean,

10:40.890 --> 10:45.312
this whole resort is incredible.

10:45.437 --> 10:48.022
Oh, that's right.

10:45.437 --> 10:48.022
You didn't live here

10:45.437 --> 10:48.022
when it was getting built.

10:48.148 --> 10:49.857
Well, it's all courtesy

10:48.148 --> 10:49.857
of Finley developments.

10:49.983 --> 10:51.901
[giggles] We have

10:49.983 --> 10:51.901
so much to catch up on.

10:52.026 --> 10:53.778
There is a ton to do

10:52.026 --> 10:53.778
around the island

10:53.903 --> 10:56.239
and of course Graham's birthday

10:53.903 --> 10:56.239
celebration's this weekend.

10:56.364 --> 10:57.991
It is the event of the summer

10:58.116 --> 10:59.951
and I have my eye on

10:58.116 --> 10:59.951
the general manager position.

11:00.076 --> 11:01.536
So if all goes well...

11:02.996 --> 11:06.166
You'll get a promotion?

11:02.996 --> 11:06.166
Ah, that's exciting.

11:06.291 --> 11:08.335
You are staying longer

11:06.291 --> 11:08.335
than three days, right?

11:08.460 --> 11:09.794
This is just a short trip.

11:09.919 --> 11:11.546
Oh, so you're not here

11:09.919 --> 11:11.546
for Graham's party?

11:11.671 --> 11:14.174
Actually, I'm here

11:11.671 --> 11:14.174
to see Chip.

11:14.299 --> 11:17.469
Oh! Oh.

11:19.053 --> 11:21.598
What does "oh" mean?

11:21.722 --> 11:24.725
You don't have a contract

11:21.722 --> 11:24.725
with you, do you?

11:25.519 --> 11:26.478
Maybe.

11:28.271 --> 11:31.525
-Let's get you a coconut.

11:28.271 --> 11:31.525
-Oh!

11:31.650 --> 11:34.944
[Gem] Do you remember how Chip

11:31.650 --> 11:34.944
was when we were kids?

11:35.069 --> 11:39.282
As a 12-year-old? Sure.

11:35.069 --> 11:39.282
Stubborn, sweet.

11:39.407 --> 11:42.827
Always took it badly

11:39.407 --> 11:42.827
when he lost at coconut toss.

11:42.952 --> 11:44.829
I'm sure he's grown up

11:42.952 --> 11:44.829
since then.

11:44.954 --> 11:46.414
Eh...

11:46.540 --> 11:49.125
I did see him on the boat

11:46.540 --> 11:49.125
from the airport

11:49.250 --> 11:52.711
and he looked pretty

11:49.250 --> 11:52.711
grown up to me.

11:52.837 --> 11:55.215
-Mmmm,

11:52.837 --> 11:55.215
-He didn't recognize me though.

11:55.340 --> 11:57.509
You two always had

11:55.340 --> 11:57.509
a thing for each other.

11:57.634 --> 12:01.971
-Oh, please, we were 12.

11:57.634 --> 12:01.971
-I know!

12:02.096 --> 12:04.599
Anyway, I think you'll find

12:02.096 --> 12:04.599
the new Chip and the old Chip

12:04.723 --> 12:06.560
have a lot in common.

12:06.685 --> 12:08.895
What's your strategy?

12:09.020 --> 12:12.982
Well, I guess if he's the old

12:09.020 --> 12:12.982
Chip then I better be

12:09.020 --> 12:12.982
the old Laura.

12:13.107 --> 12:14.568
And if he still doesn't

12:13.107 --> 12:14.568
recognize me

12:14.693 --> 12:17.820
